files.Title: Project.API.Configurations.CorsConfiguration

files.Title: Project.API.Configurations.ExecutionContextAccessor
files.Summary: Provides access to the current execution context, specifically the correlation ID from the HTTP request.

files.Title: Project.API.SeedWork.BusinessRuleValidationExceptionProblemDetails
files.Summary: Represents a standardized HTTP response for business rule validation exceptions.

files.Title: Project.API.SeedWork.InvalidCommandProblemDetails
files.Summary: Represents problem details for an error.

files.Title: Project.Api.Controllers.Users.AccountController
files.Summary: Controller responsible for handling user account-related endpoints such as registration and user info retrieval.

files.Title: Project.Api.Extensions.SwaggerExtensions
files.Summary: Provides extension methods to configure Swagger for the API.

files.Title: Project.Application.Users.IUserRepository
files.Summary: Defines the contract for user-related data operations in the domain layer.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SeedWork.BusinessRuleValidationException
files.Summary: Exception thrown when a business rule is violated. Contains the broken rule and a message describing the violation.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SeedWork.Entity
files.Summary: Represents the base class for all entities in the domain layer. Provides common behavior such as domain event handling and business rule validation.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SeedWork.IAggregateRoot
files.Summary: Marker interface used to indicate that an entity is an aggregate root. Aggregate roots are the entry point to a cluster of domain objects and enforce consistency rules.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SeedWork.IBusinessRule
files.Summary: Represents a business rule that can be validated. Business rules encapsulate domain-specific logic that must be enforced.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SeedWork.IDomainEvent
files.Summary: Represents a domain event that indicates something important has happened within the domain. Domain events are used to notify other parts of the system about changes in state.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SeedWork.INotification
files.Summary: Marker interface for domain events and notifications. Used to support the mediator pattern and event dispatching.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SeedWork.IgnoreMemberAttribute
files.Summary: Attribute used to exclude a field or property from equality and hash code calculations in value objects.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SeedWork.TypedIdValueBase
files.Summary: Base class for strongly-typed identifier value objects. Ensures consistent equality and hash code logic for identifiers.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SeedWork.ValueObject
files.Summary: Represents a base class for value objects. Value objects are immutable and compared by the values of their properties and fields.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SharedKernel.Users.Email
files.Summary: Represents a domain-specific email address value object.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SharedKernel.Users.Name
files.Summary: Represents a domain-specific name value object.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SharedKernel.Users.Rules.EmailMustBeValidRule
files.Summary: Business rule to ensure an email address is valid.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SharedKernel.Users.Rules.NameMustBeValidRule
files.Summary: Business rule to ensure a name is valid.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SharedKernel.Users.Rules.UserNameMustBeValidRule
files.Summary: Business rule to ensure a username is valid.

files.Title: Project.Domain.SharedKernel.Users.UserName
files.Summary: Represents a domain-specific username value object.

files.Title: Project.Domain.Users.User
files.Summary: Represents the application user, inheriting from IdentityUser to use ASP.NET Core Identity features directly.

files.Title: Project.Infrastructure.Database.ApplicationDbContext
files.Summary: Represents the Entity Framework Core database context for the application, integrating with ASP.NET Identity and custom domain configurations.

files.Title: Project.Infrastructure.Domain.Users.UserRepository
files.Summary: Provides an implementation of using Entity Framework Core and ASP.NET Identity.
